reviews.text: I installed two of these, one for my kitchen and one for my living room, and both rooms have recessed lighting. Unfortunately the switch is causing flickering in both rooms. I've wired dimmers before and know what I'm doing, so it's not a bad wiring job, and I'm using Phillips dimmable bulbs, so it's not the bulbs. There are certain levels of dimness where the lights don't flicker, but you have to stand there and perfect exactly where the switch lands. You can't just scroll to the exact level of dimness you want without there being flickering. Pretty frustrating and disappointing.

reviews.text: These dimmers were first appealing because they work with all modern bulb technology - incandescent, CFL, & LED. Second because this was the only place (Amazon) that I could find the quantities available for my needs. But, I ended up happily surprised by the way they look in person. I got the dark brown, and they look amazing with oil rubbed bronze wall plates. I recommend these for the price and the unexpected quality. Oh, and on the quality issue I had one in the order that was DOA. To ELEGRP's Customer service, well done! Based upon my on-line service ticket, I had a new switch in my hand the next day.
